      "span_text": "AMRICA computes the posterior probability of the alignment between the ith word of the source and jth word of the target as an equal mixture between the posterior probabilities of source-to-target and targetto-source alignments from GIZA++. 4 To obtain an approximation of the posterior probability in each direction, it uses the mbest alignments a (1). a (m), where a (k) i = j indicates that the ith source word aligns to the jth target word in the kth best alignment, and Pr(a (k) ) is the probability of the kth best alignment according to GIZA++."
